The paper deals with image resizing, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The use of Beltrami representation to preserve the geometry of important content is a novel approach that falls under the category of geometric transformations. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves interactive labeling of content regions and line structures, which falls under the category of graphics and visualization, making cs.GR (Graphics) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also involves warping maps and distortion control, which are related to multimedia and computer graphics, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CG (Computer Graphics) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper does not involve any optimization problems or tuning parameters, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category.
